Based on the interaction history, it seems that my opponent is consistently playing the move that loses to my previous move. This is supported by the fact that whenever I played rock, my opponent consistently played scissors, and when I played scissors, my opponent consistently played paper. This suggests that my opponent may be following a simple static strategy rather than adapting to my moves.
